# Rehor Dev-Bot — Impact Assessment

> Generated: {{generated_date}}

## Executive Summary

[Rehor](https://github.com/RedHatInsights/platform-frontend-ai-dev) is an autonomous AI developer bot built on Claude CLI that picks up Jira tickets, writes code, opens pull requests, and responds to code review — all without human intervention. In ~{{period_days}} days of production operation, Rehor has delivered **{{total_prmrs}}+ pull requests and merge requests** ({{total_gh_prs}} GitHub PRs + {{total_gl_mrs}} GitLab MRs) across **{{unique_repos}} repositories**, serving **10 engineering teams** from **9 production instances** deployed on Red Hat's Konflux/App-Interface infrastructure, handling **[{{total_tickets}} Jira tickets](https://redhat.atlassian.net/issues/?filter=107017)**.

> **Note:** The {{total_gh_prs}} GitHub PRs include both the dedicated bot account ([platex-rehor-bot](https://github.com/platex-rehor-bot) — [{{bot_prs_total}} PRs](https://github.com/pulls?q=is%3Apr+author%3Aplatex-rehor-bot)) and PRs opened under developer personal accounts during the pre-infrastructure period (~{{personal_prs}} additional PRs identified via Jira comment links). The {{total_gl_mrs}} GitLab MRs are internal app-interface merge requests. Not all {{total_tickets}} Jira tickets have associated PRs linked — some were grooming/triage-only, and some comment formats could not be matched automatically.

